   "id": "title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 📦 Batch Data Ingestion Pipeline — GitHub API & Open-Meteo Historical\n",
    "### Sources: GitHub REST API (public, free) + Open-Meteo Historical API (free, no key)\n",
    "### Stack: REST API → Kafka → PySpark Batch → PostgreSQL → Amazon Redshift\n",
    "### Orchestration: Apache Airflow (daily DAG)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "**Project Overview:**  \n",
    "This notebook implements a daily batch data ingestion pipeline pulling from two public sources:\n",
    "1. **GitHub REST API** — trending repositories data (stars, forks, language, contributors)\n",
    "2. **Open-Meteo Historical API** — 90-day historical weather data for 5 Indonesian cities\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is published to Kafka, processed with PySpark (batch mode), loaded to PostgreSQL, then synced to Amazon Redshift as the enterprise data warehouse.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Data Sources:**  \n",
    "- GitHub API: https://api.github.com (60 req/hour unauthenticated, 5000 with token)  \n",
    "- Open-Meteo Historical: https://archive-api.open-meteo.com (free, no key needed)"
   ]
  },
